                    <h1>Does it worth your time?</h1>
                    <p class="indent">
                        A very pretty game. The visuals are amazing. The game is a triple-A and it certainly looks like
                        one.
                        The gameplay is very very interesting for a deck building game, lots of battles and puzzles. You
                        get
                        to play with a nice variety of decks, apart from your own, and you can discover quite a few
                        winning
                        card combinations. If you never played any deck building games before and your are unsure if
                        this
                        can be your first, then I highly recommend it to you.
                    </p>
                    <p class="indent">
                        99% of the achievements will come naturally as long as you visit everything on every chapter and
                        fight every battle available. The game autosaves so you will be forced for a second playthrough
                        if
                        you miss any achievement. Although choosing the easy difficulty, the game will win the battles
                        for
                        you, speeding up the playthrough.
                    </p>
