                        discovering everything in the map. You need to acquire the Scouting ability as soon as possible,
                        talk to everybody until you exhaust their dialogue, read every notice board and fight every
                        battle
                        you encounter. The game will warn you on every point of no return and let you know how many
                        puzzles and treasure chests are left.
                    </p>
                    <p class="indent">
                        During the game you will have to make dialogue choices. Those choices will affect some
                        achievements,
                        which means if you make the 'wrong' choice, you will have to start a new playthrough, since the
                        game
                        autosaves. Finally, be careful how you spend your resources. First, upgrade everything from your
                        camp, and then craft new cards. But most likely you will have more resources than you can spend.
                    </p>
